cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as semantic role labeling. The paper also proposes a new joint optimization model designed according to the linguistic meaning of semantic role, which falls under the scope of computational linguistics. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The proposed methods also involve syntax aided learning, which falls under the scope of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well, as benchmarking is a common practice in this field.
